Europe
----------
[1] Russia (Astrachan)
Date: Tue 5 Nov 2013
Source: RG.ru Society [in Russian, trans. Mod.CP, edited]
http://www.rg.ru/2013/11/06/reg-ufo/vspyshka-anons.html


In the past 2 months, 64 cases of measles virus infection have been recorded. During this period, previously unrecognised susceptibility to measles virus infection was detected in the Roma population of the Volga and Volodarskay districts, and in [the city of] Astrachan, 26 medical students contracted the disease.

So far 15 people -- 8 children and 7 adults -- have required hospital in-patient treatment. According to the Regional Health Ministry, their condition is not giving cause for concern. At the request of the infectious diseases authorities of the Astrachan Region Ministry of Health, all necessary measures are being implemented to terminate the spread of the infection. Three days after the detection of the 1st cases of measles in the Volga Region, a total of 2200 people were examined and vaccinated.

It will be recalled that in September 2013, 26 students at the Astrakhan State Medical Academy contracted the disease. The outbreak virus had been introduced by a single student from Dagestan. Immediate steps were implemented to contain the outbreak at the Medical Academy by vaccination of students and staff.

[Byline: Nicholas Grishchenko]

--
Communicated by:
ProMED-mail
<promed@promedmail.org>

[The fact that so many of the students at the Astrachan Medical Academy contracted measles from a single student originating from an adjacent republic suggests that vaccination coverage in the Astrachan Oblast is not as comprehensive as believed by the local medical authorities.

Astrakhan is a major city in southern European Russia and the administrative center of the Astrakhan Oblast. A map and description of the Astrachan Oblast ca be accessed at: https://www.usrbc.org/russianregions/russian_regions_list/44. - Mod.CP

