[2] United Kingdom (England)
Date: Fri 8 Nov 2012
Source: Health Protection Report [edited]
http://www.hpa.org.uk/hpr/archives/2013/news4513.htm#msls1309


The declining trend in the number of laboratory confirmed cases of measles in England continued for a 5th successive month into September 2013, with only 13 new cases reported in that month.

The total number of cases for the year [2013] is 1385, unchanged from the total published to the end of August 2013. This is due to the exclusion of some cases initially classified as reactive but now reclassified. As in August 2013, the South-West region reported the most cases in September 2013, and almost all of these were associated with an on-going outbreak of a new D8 strain in the area. A few sporadic cases were detected in other regions.

So far this year [2013], 271 (20 percent) confirmed cases have been associated with primary and secondary school outbreaks. Small outbreaks have also been reported from "hard-to-reach" populations with known low vaccine coverage such as the travelling community and the ultra-Orthodox Jewish community in north London. Overall, 295 (21 percent) of all cases in 2013 were admitted to hospital; 47 reported complications including pneumonia, meningitis and gastroenteritis.

--
