[4] Ukraine (Rovensskoi oblast)
Date: Mon 4 Nov 2013
Source: RIA Novosti - Ukraine [machine trans. edited]


A measles outbreak was reported on Mon 4 Nov 2013 by the Ukrainian Ministry of Health. A total of 42 children have been affected. Between 23-28 Oct 2013, a total of 42 children contracted measles, according to the statement.

As of Monday [4 Nov 2013], all patients with a mild form of the disease are in out-patient treatment. The General Directorate of the GosSanEpidemNadzor in the Rovenskoia Oblast created a rapid response team to investigate the causes of the disease. The epidemiological investigation established that 9 individuals had been fully vaccinated according to the recommendations of the national immunization schedule; 4 had received a single vaccination only, and the remaining 29 had not been vaccinated. Where appropriate, revaccination is being undertaken.

--
Communicated by:
ProMED-Rus <promed@promedmail.org>

[In the Ukraine, routine vaccination against measles is held twice: at 12-15 months and at 6 years, but for unexplained reasons, some children at this school had not received the recommended course of vaccinations.

A political map of Ukraine, showing the location of Rovenskoi oblast in the north, can be accessed at: http://www.mapsofworld.com/ukraine/ukraine-political-map.html. - Mod.CP

