Alberta Health Service [AHS] s says there have been 19 confirmed cases of measles in southern Alberta, including the Lethbridge area, but suspects there are many more cases that have gone unreported. AHS says several homes are under quarantine. The age of the patients ranges from 4 years old to 23. None of the patients had received measles vaccine.

